Hindustan Zinc Profit Jumps on Higher Prices of Zinc, Silver

-- B y   A b h i s h e k   S h a n k e r
-- 
2011-07-21T08:57:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-21/hindustan-zinc-profit-jumps-on-higher-prices-of-zinc-silver-1-.html
Hindustan Zinc Ltd. (HZ) ,  India â€™s largest
producer, reported a 67 percent increase in first-quarter profit
as zinc and silver prices gained.  Net income climbed to 14.9 billion rupees ($335 million),
or 3.54 rupees a share, in the three months ended June 30 from
8.91 billion rupees, or 2.11 rupees, a year earlier, the unit of
London-based  Vedanta Resources Plc (VED)  said today in a statement to
the Bombay Stock Exchange. The average of 16 analyst estimates
compiled by Bloomberg was 13.5 billion rupees. Sales increased
45 percent to 28.2 billion rupees.  The average price of silver, the precious metal the company
also produces, more than doubled to $38.5 an ounce in the
quarter in the cash market, while prices of zinc, required to
rust-proof steel, averaged 10 percent higher at $2,272 a metric
ton in  London .  Shares of the Udaipur, Rajasthan-based company gained as
much as 3.2 percent to 141.50 rupees and traded at 138.65 rupees
as of 1:55 p.m. in Mumbai. The benchmark Sensitive Index of the
Bombay Stock Exchange fell 0.2 percent.  Total expenses rose 31 percent to 13.9 billion rupees in
the quarter on higher royalty and coal prices. Coal gained 21
percent to an average $120 a ton from a year earlier, according
to researcher McCloskey Group Ltd.  To contact the reporter on this story:
